🔥OLD SCHOOL VEGETABLE SOUP 🔥 (The video will be uploaded to my YouTube channel tonight at 5:30PM CST) 

* This is the soup that will comfort you on a cold or rainy day. 

* This is the soup that you loved as a kid growing up in the South, but would only have the luxury of eating if your grandma or auntie made it.

*This is the soup that even though it’s called vegetable soup, black people still find a way to throw some meat in there.. 🤷🏾‍♀️🥸😵‍💫😂

* This is the soup that feels like home and hugs. 

* This is also the soup that you need to jump on now and make! I hope that you all had a great holiday and a great start to your New Year! Last year was a WILD ONE for me personally. I’ve learned a lot and made a lot of life changes ! It’s been rough but we made it! 

While experiencing my current part of life , it’s been a STRUGGLE trying to do the things that make me happy and bring me joy! (Even cooking.) I asked myself, what could I make that would just give me the feel goods and make me want to regain that joy again and I was led this soup believe it or not. 

My recipes are more than just posting for IG likes and views on YouTube. Many of them like this one is NOSTALGIC for me and help me to express exactly how I’m feeling through flavors and whatever else I’m feeling in that moment. 

This soup was definitely the comforting hug I needed to get through a rough patch and I hope that y’all enjoy the recipe. (When I post it tonight on YouTube! 😵‍💫) In the meantime, enjoy the feels!

🔥 THE BEST JUICY & CRISPY BAKED CHICKEN 🔥 (Check out the full video recipe on my YouTube channel by clicking the link in my bio!)

BaKEd cHIcKeN?!? You say? 

First of all, this has to be the most COMMON way to cook chicken yet it has been the most complicated recipe to NAIL when it comes to juiciness and crispiness! 

Have you ever had baked chicken that was surely tasty, but the skin was SLIMY 😵‍💫 or the meat was DRY as Goat hair? 😩

I know you have and you might’ve even made some like that yourself, but guess what? I have something GOOD to tell ya! There’s a way to keep your chicken JUICY while still obtaining that crispy skin that we all love! Oh and don’t forget the FLAVOR! Not just on the top layer, but literally EVERY BITE! 

My favorite piece of the chicken is the THICK THIGHS.. what’s yours? Drop your fave part of the chicken to eat in the comments if you’re ready to upgrade and elevate your chicken recipe!

🔥 SOUTHERN STYLE BEEF NECK BONES 🔥 (Check out the full recipe on my YouTube channel by clicking the link in my bio or story! ) 

FIRST OFF, I bet you ain’t NEVA seen a plate of neck bones this pretty 😍! Lol. Let me take you WAY BACK in time before oxtails we’re even a big deal! These cheap cuts of meat ($3-$5 per pack) were top tier in a Southern household on a Sunday evening and literally give me all the nostalgic feels ! 😩

And if you’ve never had them, hunny you don’t even know what you’re missing! If your grandma or auntie never cooked you a pot of neck bones and rice then I’m sorry, but guess what, here’s your chance to shine now! I have curated a recipe based off of my experience as a young southern girl and what I remember to be the one of the best most INEXPENSIVE yet fulfilling meal ever! 

My aunt would make neck bones and add the rice into the gravy which is also another way to enjoy them! 

Check out all the deets on how I made this delicious meal for Sunday dinner on my YouTube channel! The link is in my story as well as my bio! Enjoy loves!

🔥 LUNCHTIME SAMMICH 🔥

TRUTH IS… It’s lunchtime and I’m hungry…(I’m always hungry 😩) but honestly, I don’t always cook as much as people think I do but when I’m NOT ordering DoorDash or cooking meals for a my channel, I’m usually making a sandwich and chips or ramen to save the day… 

… and believe it or not, this grinder salad sandwich STILLLLL has me in a complete chokehold. It requires little effort, it’s customizable, and it packs a whole lot of flavor! 

I recorded a VoiceOver for this video maybe 40 times and decided to just NOT because I always sound like cornbread and 1 minute is NEVER enough for ME to talk lol 😂 I didn’t want to call this a grinder because SOMEBODY, SOMEWHERE is gonna hit me with a , “ That’s not a grinder..” and I’m not up for it today lol so we’re going with it just being a SAMMICH, because then you can’t tell me how to make my own SAMMICH 😂🤷🏾‍♀️… See what I did there? Lol. 

Y’all enjoy this beautiful Tuesday and stock up on your allergy meds! The pollen takeover has begun! 😂😵‍💫

🔥 SUPER EASY KOREAN CORNDOGS! MY WAY (1st Attempt) 🔥

Soooo let me tell you about the time that I had these for the first time ever! I was in Austin, Texas at the H-Mart and it was the best bite I ever experienced along with Korean Fried Chicken! 

There were A LOT of toppings to choose from and while I feel that the sugar DOES work with the saltiness of the hotdog, I just can bring myself to add it on these lol 😂. 

These are a super lazy and inauthentic version for people at home like me because if I would’ve jacked this up, I would’ve been too mad lol. Deciding to use the crescent dough wasn’t as nearly a half bad idea. It actually worked well and gave the sweet dough feel. Obviously it’s not as fluffy as the original dough but it works! Maybe I’ll make the dough in another video soon! 

But in the meantime, you guys should definitely try these at home. They’re super fun to make and highly customizable… if you’re lactose intolerant, mmhmnh, get somebody else to do it..!!! 😩😩😩 

Enjoy!

🔥 AMAZING MISSISSIPPI POT ROAST MY WAY! 🔥 (Check out the full video recipe on my YouTube channel!) 

Hey y’all! So listen! I just made this delicious Mississippi Pot roast per request ( SHOUT OUT TO MY GOOD MAN @terrellparson_ 😩❤️) and I’m GLADDDD about it! 

Everyone who has asked me about making this all had the same thing in common. They said that the original recipe is not as impressive as they thought and felt that it lacked SOMETHING … so you know that’s where I come in right? 😌😏😏😏

This roast follows the same concept but uses wayyyy more flavor and has A LOT more love, I mean look at her! 😩

I’m gonna tell you now, there is definitely more than just 5 ingredients but only because I wanted to rely on creating most of the flavor myself than to use the traditional au jus and/ or brown gravy packets. 

ALSO, I actually cooked this on the stovetop and I prefer this method over all other methods because I can manipulate this roast however I want to while cooking! I also made the gravy a thicker consistency than what the regular MS roast may call for! Both choices were EXCELLENT decisions as you can see and I can’t wait for y’all to try this one here! 

ANDDD MIGHT I ADD, if you’re one of my kinfolk who doesn’t want to babysit this roast for 3 hours, I added cooking instructions and temps for the crockpot, instapot, and oven in my video! It’s embedded there so you’ll have to watch to see 😁😉😜! 

PS: Best practice for leftovers are SANDWICHES . 

Y’all enjoy! Byeeeee!

🔥 KAYLA’S SOUTHERN STYLE CHICKEN SALAD 🔥 (Check out the full video recipe on my YouTube channel by clicking the link in my bio!) 

Y’all might as well dance yourselves right on to the grocery store, get a rotisserie and make one of these “Chicken Salad” 💁🏾‍♀️💁🏾‍♀️💁🏾‍♀️. And this AIN’T NO 81st deli neither lol 🤭. For all of my kinfolk who were watching my live yesterday, I stayed up extra late to make sure I got this ready for you guys and I’m glad about it because you’re going to LOVEEEEE IT! 

So listen, there are a few things….. 

I’ve eaten MANY variations of chicken salad in my lifetime, and I must say, the Southern way is just HOME! 

The use of boiled eggs, sweet pickle, duke’s, and onion makes this a true southern salad fasho! Now some of y’all may be wondering🙆🏾‍♀️, where is the bell pepper, raw onion, and celery?? While that is somewhat traditional where I live, I am just really against raw, crunchy, chunky, veggies in my chicken salad, potato salad, and even deviled eggs! 😩😩😩 I just can’t do it y’all, but if that’s your preference, you know you can always add them in, but for ME AND MY HOUSE?? AHT AHT 😂

Oh, and don’t forget that sugar in the end! We like it savory with a touch of sweet where I’m from! 🔥❤️

So now that all of that is said, I need y’all to head over to my YouTube channel and check out the full video recipe to get all the deets and measurements to make this delicious meal! I’m gonna go have me a sammich in a minute and I’m the meanwhile, tell me in the comments how you like to eat your chicken salad! Crackers vs Bread? 

Love y’all! Bye!

🔥 VIRAL GUMBO GREENS 🥬🔥 
(Check out the full video recipe on my YouTube channel by clicking the link in my bio!)

Sooooooo, I’ve been seeing these greens all over the place and I’m going to be honest with you. I immediately thought to myself, absolutely NOT ! 

HOWEVER…..

With a simple request from @terrellparson_ and a little work, These bad boys turned out to be some of the most delicious greens I’ve ever tasted in my life and I’m serious! I had my reservations about the shrimp, and that still stands. If I ever make them again, which I’m sure I will, I will definitely leave it out. It’s mostly because I just don’t care for shrimp and it really just doesn’t fit to me, but that’s my opinion. 

Now before y’all go all haywire like this is an abomination or absolutely ludicrous, let’s state facts! One, we pay respect and homage to originality over here and while this is an inauthentic “TikTok” version, this recipe is actually real and inspired by a New Orleans dish called “Gumbo Z’Herbes” created by Chef Leah Chase (1941) of Dooky Chase’s Restaurant! The original dish is inspired by several cuisines and includes multiple types of greens that are cooked down in a roux with herbs, spices, and the holy trinity. The original does not include meat usually, but there are some variations with smoked meats and sausages. 

I’m gonna tell you now, it’s definitely worth at least 1 shot and if you don’t like it, I bet it won’t be because of the flavor because it is ALL THERE! Check out “MY VERSION” of how I pay homage to this delicious and inspiring recipe on my YouTube channel this evening! I’ll be dropping the video at 4:30CST so be on the look out guys!!

Someone requested this whole jerk turkey and hunny when I tell you it is BOMB? HUNNY! 

I mean; I could definitely see a whole Caribbean inspired Thanksgiving meal in the near future. Makes perfect sense right? The combination of seasonings and fresh aromatics is worked amazingly together and taking the time to really care for this bird makes the whole difference! 

In most households where I live, we usually fry our turkey in peanut oil with Cajun seasonings until golden brown crispy perfection. Most times, that does NOT require a brine, but in my personal and humble opinion, if you’re gonna bake a turkey, DEFINITELY do not skip the brine! 

I used a non traditional brine to accent the citrus flavors that are usually used when cooking jerk and baby lemme tell you…. PICASSO! 

This recipe would also work with a whole chicken if you’re not into turkey! But aside from all the talk, just make sure that you are present and accounted for when this video drops today! This 60second clip does not explain nearly half of what this amazing process takes!
